author: Inside Edition
description: In a medical mystery, someone was slowly poisoning 26-year-old mother Hannah Pettey. Pettey lost a lot of weight, ending up weighing just 84 pounds. She was finally hospitalized with acute respiratory failure and kept alive on a ventilator. She was then diagnosed with lead poisoning. CBS News correspondent Anne Marie Green is investigating the case for a "48 Hours" episode airing Saturday and spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall. Pettey made a full recovery, but the mystery remained: who poisoned her?
title: Who Poisoned 26-Year-Old Hannah Pettey?

author: Inside Edition
description: A 550-pounds unbearable house guest was forced to flee after squatting for more than a month. It took Operation Paintball to finally cast out the intruder. For more than a month, the bear settled in a crawl space under a home in Altadena, California. Finally, homeowner Ken Johnson was contacted by the non-profit group Bear League. The group works to keep bears out of places where they don't belong. They fired paintballs into the dirt in the crawl space and the bear scrambled out.
title: Bear That Settled Under California Home For A Month Finally Leaves

author: Inside Edition
description: A woman vacationing in the US Virgin Islands was attacked by a shark while snorkeling. Another tourist heard the screams and ran into the water, stuffing a pool noodle into the back of his swim trunks as a life preserver. Christopher Carroll is a surgical nurse and one-time lifeguard from Utah. Carroll told EMS that the shark took the woman's left arm. The victim has been identified as 56-year-old Arlene Lillis, a pharmacist from Minnesota. Lillis did not survive the shark attack.
title: Minnesota Woman Dies After Shark Attack in US Virgin Islands

author: Inside Edition
description: For nearly two decades, smoking has been out of fashion, but now, pop culture appears to romanticize the deadly habit. It is alarming because cigarette smoking is the leading cause of preventable deaths in the US with more than 480,000 Americans dying every year. The rise in smoking in TV and films is concerning health experts across the country. Michael Seilback of the American Lung Association spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Are Cigarettes Cool Again?

author: Inside Edition
description: Newly released video recorded by the ICE agent shows what happened from the point of view of the agent in the moments before he fatally shot Minneapolis mom of three, Renee Good. Good's wife stood on the street, also recording the agent. The agent walked to the front of the SUV and that was when GoHandoutod hit the gas and the agent was jostled. Thursday night, late night comics blasted the Trump Administration.
title: Cell Phone Video Recorded By ICE Agent Who Killed Renee Good Released

author: Inside Edition
description: A neighbor leapt into action when he saw a house on fire. A mother and her two children were trapped on the third floor. The mother dropped one of the kids into the arms of the neighbor on the ground outside. Fifteen seconds later, she dropped the second kid safely. Other neighbors were able to get a ladder and the mother climbed down to safety. Inside Edition spoke to Ashley Gubernat and her 9-year-old son Wyatt outside her fire-ravaged home near Baltimore and hero neighbor Steven Angelini.
title: Hero Neighbor Catches Children From Burning House

author: Inside Edition
description: A hiker spotted a dog in peril, stranded on a cliff. The hiker called for the frightened German shepherd to come down. She posted the video of a distressed dog seeking help on the animal rescue site "I Love Rescue." Hours later, two Good Samaritans got to a location in Hesperia, California. Aaron Christensen and Mark Primasing say the conditions were treacherous. Finally, Christensen was able to get the dog but then both men and the dog were trapped. Eventually, they were all rescued.
title: Man Arrested After Attempting To Rescue Dog From Steep Cliff

author: Inside Edition
description: The 37-year-old mother was shot and killed by an ICE agent in Minneapolis earlier this week.
title: Who Was Renee Nicole Good? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Reality TV star Bethenny Frankel says she picked up the rash while ringing in the New Year at a hotel in St. Barths, a Caribbean island popular amongst billionaires.
title: Bethenny Frankel Got Rash From St. Barths Hotel Sheets #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: This family is going for the gold! Meet the Alpine Ski Team that wants to represent the nation of Jamaica in the Winter Olympics. 18 year-old triplets Helaina, Henri, and Henniyah Rivers, all New York-born and bred, were brought up with a love of winter sports. So why Jamaica? Well, that's where their mother is from. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 18-Year-Old Skiing Triplets Training To Compete In Winter Olympics For Jamaica

author: Inside Edition
description: What's the hurry? The Washington State Patrol says this driver was clocked at 156 miles per hour on I-5 on New Year's Eve. A patrolman attempted to pull the car over, but it was going too fast and authorities were unable to locate it.
title: Speeding Car Reaches 156 MPH On Highway #shorts
